        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(lmstudio): deliver thinking \"off\" to binary-thinking models",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes LM Studio binary-thinking models ignoring explicit `thinking: off`.\n- Adds a purpose-built supported SDK helper on the lightweight `provider-stream-shared` subpath that only patches existing `reasoning_effort` fields on `openai-completions` payloads when the requested thinking level is exactly `off`.\n- Composes that helper in the LM Studio provider hook for both preload-enabled and preload-disabled paths.\n- Maps disabled intent through the discovered model compatibility map (`none` for current LM Studio), or removes `reasoning_effort` when the model has no disabled value.\n- Leaves the general OpenAI thinking wrapper and official OpenAI/Anthropic provider paths unchanged.\n\nThe issue suggested sending LM Studio's discovered `off` value directly. Live LM Studio rejects that API value; its Chat Completions schema accepts `none`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, and `xhigh`. The model metadata's `off`/`on` values describe model capability, while `reasoning_effort: \"none\"` is the valid wire value that disables thinking.\n\nCloses #91913.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: An embedded/local LM Studio run with `--thinking off` previously retained the transport's enabled `reasoning_effort`, causing binary-thinking models to fall back to thinking on.\n\nReal environment tested: LM Studio with `qwen/qwen3-0.6b` Q8_0, advertising `allowed_options: [\"off\", \"on\"]`, plus live official OpenAI and Anthropic API calls.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-lmstudio-e2e-92002 pnpm openclaw agent --local --agent main --session-id 7efb51fd-88fa-4a39-8520-ffa26427fc6f --model lmstudio/qwen/qwen3-0.6b --thinking off --message 'Reply with the single word OK.' --timeout 120 --json`\n\nEvidence after fix: The LM Studio request log captured exactly one request containing `\"reasoning_effort\": \"none\"` and no unsupported-reasoning fallback warning. The OpenClaw result reported provider `lmstudio`, model `qwen/qwen3-0.6b`, visible response `OK.`, stop reason `stop`, and `reasoningTokens: 0`.\n\nObserved result after fix: Explicit thinking off completes end to end with no reasoning output and no LM Studio fallback to thinking on.\n\nWhat was not tested: The reporter's 26B Gemma model was not downloaded; the live model exposes the same binary reasoning metadata and exercises the same request-shaping path. No live active-memory plugin call was required because the local embedded agent command drives the affected provider stream hook directly.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Focused Vitest lanes: 5 shards, 401 tests passed.\n- Official OpenAI live tool projection: 3/3 passed, including Responses function calls, GPT-5.5 Chat Completions function calls, and code-mode projection after an unreadable sibling.\n- Official Anthropic live tool replay: 3/3 passed, including regular replay, omitted-reasoning replay, and `toolCall`/`toolResult` replay.\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm docs:check-links`\n- Focused `oxfmt`, `oxlint`, and `git diff --check`\n- Fresh autoreview against current `origin/main`: no actionable findings.\n- Full local build passed; bundle inspection confirmed LM Studio does not load the broad proxy/OpenAI transport wrapper graph.\n- Remote build and changed gate: Crabbox/Testbox `run_67c58b44dac3` (running).\n\n## Risk\n\nThe helper is opt-in and LM Studio is its only consumer. It returns the original stream for every thinking level except explicit `off`, ignores non-Chat-Completions APIs, and only rewrites an already-present `reasoning_effort` field. Official OpenAI and Anthropic tool-calling paths are not routed through it and were live-tested separately.\n\nContributor live proof also covered LM Studio 0.4.16 on Linux with the same Qwen model and observed the same corrected `reasoning_effort: \"none\"` request.\n",
